headline: Texas Attempt to Kickstart New Gas-Fired Power Is Stumbling
summary: (Bloomberg) -- A Texas experiment to fund new natural gas-burning power plants with $5 billion in public loans is faltering as several of the proposed facilities drop out, threatening the state’s efforts to meet growing electricity demand.
